news.title: Uttarakhand likely to tighten law on land sale to outsiders
news.para: But local residents are now demanding that power to buy land even in municipal areas be curtailed to 250 sqm and a complete ban be imposed on sale of land in rural areas.

news.title: BofA leases 1.1 million sq ft office space in Chennai
news.para: In the first phase, the company will occupy around 710,000 sq ft, while the remaining 390,000 sq ft in part of the second phase expansion option by the multinational bank, as per the registered document.

news.title: Kansai Nerolac Paints to sell land parcel to Aethon Developers for Rs 726 crore
news.para: "The board of directors have approved a proposal for monetization of idle land parcels of the company not being put for productive use," Kansai Nerolac Paints said in a BSE filing.

news.title: NBCC sells 5,000 flats of Amrapali for Rs 2,900 crore
news.para: ​As per the direction of the Supreme Court, Amrapali Stalled Projects Investments Reconstruction Establishment (ASPIRE) was formed to complete the stuck projects of Amrapali through NBCC (India) Ltd.

news.title: Noida, Greater Noida authority paves way to restart stuck housing projects
news.para: In their board meeting on Tuesday, both the authorities gave final approval which will allow builders to take benefit of zero period, more time for payment of dues, permission to mortgage among others.

news.title: Suraj Estate Developers' shares make disappointing market debut; settle with over 7% discount
news.para: ​A​t the BSE, the stock made its debut at Rs 343.80, a discount of 4.5 per cent from the issue price. During the day, shares of the company plunged 10 per cent to Rs 323.95 before settling at Rs 334.30, down by 7.13 per cent.

news.title: Delhi High Court allows retired BSF employees to complete stuck housing project
news.para: The members had entered into an agreement with the builder in 2006 for the purchase of 266 flats in the project for Rs 65 crore, and the flats were to be handed over by June, 2010.

news.title: MahaRERA recovers nearly Rs 140 crore as homebuyers' compensation through warrants
news.para: The authority has issued 1,123 warrants so far this year to recover nearly Rs 764 crore from developers for the delay in the handing over of the apartments, with a warning to freeze their bank accounts and attach assets.

news.title: Jaipur zonal master plan for seven eco-sensitive zones released
news.para: An official stated, “The Zonal Master Plans of eco-sensitive zones address all key development issues, including land use, infrastructure, and transportation, with a primary focus on ecology, environment, and wildlife.”

news.title: Fundraise by Damji Shamji Realty rated 'D' a sign of junk bond market breaking free
news.para: Recently, a real estate company with a D rating (indicating default) raised ₹95 crore from the private placement bond market - sending early signs of the evolution of the junk bond market in India.

news.title: Greater Noida to appoint private company to draw up citizen-centric initiatives, SOPs
news.para: Two of the teams will assist the planning and project departments, and the third will work directly with upper management — officers on special duty, additional CEOs, and the CEO — to oversee priority tasks and requirements from other departments.

news.title: Mega sealing drive against Panchkula property tax defaulters on January 1
news.para: Mayor Kulbhushan Goyal, while sharing the information, stated that the MC had planned a major property sealing drive of property tax defaulters on January 1, 2024.

news.title: Thane civic chief warns officials of action for laxity in tackling unauthorised construction
news.para: ​The diktat comes a day after he sent a senior Thane Municipal Corporation official on "compulsory leave" for allegedly protecting illegal structures.

news.title: One in two properties in Bengaluru not paying annual tax
news.para: According to BBMP data, there are 13.4 lakh 'A' khata properties and 6.8 lakh 'B' khata properties in the city. The data shows that only 20.2 lakh properties having 'A' or 'B' khata are paying property taxes to the civic agency.

news.title: Delhi LG directs officials to come up with time-bound plan for unauthorised colonies regularisation
news.para: The officials said that he took stock of the progress and status of works related to regularisation of the unauthorized colonies and rehabilitation of the slum dwellers under the PM-UDAY and PMAY (Urban) respectively.

news.title: MMRDA picked for development of Malad land at meet chaired by Maharashtra CM, DCM
news.para: The land has huge commercial potential as it is located on Mumbai’s coast and offers transport connectivity via Metro 2A (Dahisar to D N Nagar) and the proposed Coastal road, sources said.

news.title: Hand over Indirapuram to Ghaziabad civic body by Feb 2024, Uttar Pradesh CM tells GDA
news.para: The CM, who was in NCR for Gautam Buddha University’s annual convocation ceremony on Sunday, briefly met Sahibabad MLA Sunil Sharma and BJP councillors from Indirapuram over the issue.

news.title: Mumbai: Sai Estate consultant's properties seized over loan default
news.para: ​The action was taken under the Securitisation and Reconstruction of Financial Assets and Enforcement of Security Interest (SARFAESI) Act , 2002.

news.title: Fine Future scam: Seven attached properties auctioned for Rs 4 crore
news.para: Earlier, the Economic Offences Wing (EOW) police had attached 140 properties belonging to the managing directors and agents of Fine Future firm for duping investors of ₹189.15 crore.

news.title: Ludhiana: FIR against two Malakpur residents in Rs 13 crore land fraud
news.para: It has been alleged that the accused, who are farmers, took the money against 64 kanals near South City from Ashok Kumar of Rishi Nagar.
